external_knowledge:
; A 'season' refers to a fixed period in a year when a particular sport is played; 
; 'leading scorers' refers to the players who scored the most points in the season; 
; 'played more than a dozen games' refers to the condition that a player must have played in more than 10 games to be considered.

sql:
SELECT team_id, win_percentage
FROM team_standings
WHERE standing_id = 1;

SELECT games_played
FROM games_played
WHERE team_id = 1 AND season_id = 1;

external_knowledge:
Braved the toughest storms: This metaphorical expression refers to teams that have played against strong opponents with a high strength of schedule and a high number of points scored per game by their opponents; 
Season of fire: This expression refers to a specific season, in this case, season_id = 2; 
Defensive resilience: This refers to the ability of a team to limit the number of points scored by their opponents.
